@startuml BorrowBook
title Activity Diagram: Borrow Book

' Description:
' This activity diagram describes the process of borrowing a book in the Library Management System.
' Steps:
' 1. Member searches for a book by title, author, or ISBN.
' 2. System checks if the book is available in the catalog.
' 3. If not available, system notifies the member and ends the process.
' 4. If available, member requests to borrow the book.
' 5. System verifies member account status (active, no overdue books exceeding limit).
' 6. If account is invalid or blocked, system notifies the member and ends the process.
' 7. System creates a loan record with due date (typically 14 days).
' 8. System decrements the available copy count of the book.
' 9. System confirms the loan to the member with due date information.
' 10. Activity ends.

|Member|
start
:Search for Book;
|System|
:Check Book Availability;
if (Book Available?) then (yes)
  |Member|
  :Request to Borrow;
  |System|
  :Verify Member Account;
  if (Account Valid?) then (yes)
    :Create Loan Record;
    :Update Book Copy Count;
    :Send Confirmation & Due Date;
    |Member|
    :Receive Confirmation;
  else (no)
    :Notify Account Issue;
    |Member|
    :Notified of Block;
  endif
else (no)
  :Notify Unavailable;
  |Member|
  :Notified Unavailable;
endif
stop
@enduml
